verbose_text: Twenty-four hour mean blood glucose levels were modestly lower during OL compared with CL control on both sedentary (135 +/- 46 vs. 140 +/- 47 mg/dL, P = 0.02) and exercise (141 +/- 63 vs. 147 +/- 56 mg/dL, P = 0.04) days, but these differences disappeared when blood glucose levels < 70 mg/dL were removed from the analyses.
